The Song of Youth.

880
00:37:07,330 --> 00:37:10,250
You were once a seed

881
00:37:10,620 --> 00:37:12,190
buried in the soil,

882
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:15,150
1uietly waiting to sprout.

883
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:18,020
The first spring rain

884
00:37:18,290 --> 00:37:23,000
brought you your first hope for life.

885
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:26,680
-Ms. Han.
-Ms. Han.

886
00:37:26,710 --> 00:37:27,850
Hello, Ms. Han.

887
00:37:29,180 --> 00:37:30,370
Don't be nervous.

888
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:32,380
Just look it over a few more times.

889
00:37:35,690 --> 00:37:37,550
Lead the reading well, good luck!

890
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:42,840
Youth is like a song,

891
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:46,680
resonating in our hearts.

892
00:37:46,730 --> 00:37:49,770
Youth is like a poem,

893
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:52,140
full of passion,

894
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:54,450
and words overflowing with energy.

895
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:57,930
The flowing notes

896
00:37:57,950 --> 00:38:00,950
etch the light of life

897
00:38:00,990 --> 00:38:04,030
on the walls of time

898
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:08,320
with an unfeeling brushstroke.

899
00:38:08,980 --> 00:38:11,660
Dreams stir within us.

900
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:15,520
Courage is a precious asset.

901
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:19,200
Let us sail forward with courage,

902
00:38:19,390 --> 00:38:20,820
for only by staying true to our ideals

903
00:38:20,820 --> 00:38:23,490
can we truly embody the best of youth.

904
00:38:23,650 --> 00:38:28,200
Let us spread the wings of our youth,

905
00:38:28,350 --> 00:38:30,760
and rise with the wind.

906
00:38:33,480 --> 00:38:34,020
Good.

907
00:38:43,740 --> 00:38:44,750
Guys, hurry up.

908
00:38:47,930 --> 00:38:49,310
Did I do alright just now?

909
00:38:49,310 --> 00:38:49,940
Yes!

910
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:51,510
Thank you.

911
00:39:03,100 --> 00:39:03,870
Why hasn't your brother's class

912
00:39:03,870 --> 00:39:04,630
gone on yet?

913
00:39:04,630 --> 00:39:05,420
They are here.

914
00:39:05,420 --> 00:39:06,520
-Now, please enjoy
-Get ready to applaud.

915
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:08,560
the poetry reading

916
00:39:08,590 --> 00:39:09,870
by Class 1, Grade 10:

917
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:10,770
The Seabird,

918
00:39:10,790 --> 00:39:12,370
led by Yuan Shanqing.

919
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:26,680
Wait,

920
00:39:26,710 --> 00:39:28,390
why don't they have red cheeks?

921
00:39:28,390 --> 00:39:30,190
Shh, don't talk, it's starting.

922
00:39:30,370 --> 00:39:31,800
So what if they don't?

923
00:39:38,730 --> 00:39:39,730
The Seabird.

924
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,280
Migration

925
00:39:42,650 --> 00:39:44,510
is the destiny of the Arctic Tern.

926
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:47,100
When winter arrives,

927
00:39:47,530 --> 00:39:49,340
they begin their long journey,

928
00:39:50,160 --> 00:39:51,360
skimming over waves,

929
00:39:51,710 --> 00:39:52,970
crossing the equator,

930
00:39:53,630 --> 00:39:54,890
and flying southward,

931
00:39:55,430 --> 00:39:56,970
from the northern hemisphere

932
00:39:56,970 --> 00:39:59,300
to the warmth of the southern hemisphere.

933
00:40:00,650 --> 00:40:01,890
Every migration

934
00:40:02,260 --> 00:40:04,470
is an 18,000-kilometer journey.

935
00:40:05,670 --> 00:40:06,910
Every journey

936
00:40:07,310 --> 00:40:09,710
is the fiery passage from winter to summer.

937
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,730
Every fiery passage

938
00:40:12,310 --> 00:40:15,040
is the greatness of a small life that never stops.

939
00:40:15,430 --> 00:40:16,830
Our lives

940
00:40:16,980 --> 00:40:19,980
have never been calm waters.
Passing through thorns.

941
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:22,720
The young cross mountains and seas,

942
00:40:22,870 --> 00:40:24,400
passing through thorns.

943
00:40:24,980 --> 00:40:27,950
Along the way, they plant flowers.

944
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:31,380
They clear stones on the mountainsides.

945
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:34,990
They raise sails in rushing rivers.

946
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:38,660
They no longer look back in the mud.

947
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:40,450
Do you remember

948
00:40:40,470 --> 00:40:43,560
those youngsters who clenched their fists and said,

949
00:40:43,780 --> 00:40:44,930
"When I grow up,

950
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:46,920
I will forge ahead,

951
00:40:47,140 --> 00:40:49,060
like the first seabird,

952
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:51,230
spreading my trembling wings."

953
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:53,850
The seabirds gather in the south.

954
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,760
We will finally reunite

955
00:40:55,790 --> 00:40:58,340
in a sea of flowers in the high mountains.

956
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:02,060
The spring breeze, oblivious to its own charm,

957
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:03,720
stirs the hearts of the young.

958
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:06,590
Summer generously extends the day,

959
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,640
warming the love of the seabird.

960
00:41:09,080 --> 00:41:11,330
A seabird is still a seabird,

961
00:41:11,580 --> 00:41:13,150
unafraid of thunder and rain,

962
00:41:13,150 --> 00:41:14,550
undeterred by distance.

963
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:17,120
A youth is still a youth,

964
00:41:17,490 --> 00:41:19,140
like wild grass in the wasteland,

965
00:41:19,140 --> 00:41:21,870
the midsummer in their hearts cannot be cut down.

966
00:41:22,010 --> 00:41:23,120
Oh, wind and rain,

967
00:41:23,430 --> 00:41:25,390
please be kind to every

968
00:41:25,420 --> 00:41:26,860
flying seabird.

969
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,550
Oh, youth,

970
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:31,790
please be kind to those young and bold days.

971
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:35,250
May you soar freely,

972
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:38,760
brave and free like the seabird.

973
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:46,210
You shout.

974
00:41:48,830 --> 00:41:49,380
Sit down.

975
00:41:52,050 --> 00:41:52,770
Okay.

976
00:41:53,290 --> 00:41:56,120
Bravo! Bravo!

977
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:09,880
I will now announce the results of the competition.

978
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:11,160
First prize in the Linqi Second High School's

979
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:14,360
Red October Poetry Reading Competition goes to…

980
00:42:15,060 --> 00:42:16,270
Class 1, Grade 10,

981
00:42:16,300 --> 00:42:17,360
for "The Seabird."

982
00:42:23,770 --> 00:42:25,070
Back then, when we were young,

983
00:42:25,070 --> 00:42:26,870
we always shouted slogans,

984
00:42:27,380 --> 00:42:28,690
filled with ideals,

985
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:30,120
yearning to fly free.

986
00:42:30,510 --> 00:42:31,840
We wanted to break through

987
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,280
all the obstacles

988
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,750
and dreamed of the world beyond.

989
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:37,200
But I forgot

990
00:42:37,450 --> 00:42:39,110
that this small base was home.

991
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:41,470
At 17, we thought

992
00:42:41,470 --> 00:42:43,220
we were already grown up,

993
00:42:43,260 --> 00:42:44,140
mature,

994
00:42:44,490 --> 00:42:45,890
that we understood love,

995
00:42:45,900 --> 00:42:46,920
understood the future,

996
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:49,250
understood the migration of the seabird.

997
00:42:49,820 --> 00:42:50,540
Later,

998
00:42:51,710 --> 00:42:53,620
I really did see many,

999
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,840
many seabirds flying across the ocean.

1000
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:56,980
But at that moment,

1001
00:42:57,430 --> 00:42:58,880
what I missed most was

1002
00:42:59,540 --> 00:43:00,710
that day,

1003
00:43:01,010 --> 00:43:02,480
when everyone had their faces painted red,

1004
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:03,440
like actors in a play.
